== Roasted Potatoes ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} diced into ½-inch pieces; toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Lemony Broccoli ==

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and mince @Shallot{1}. Strip @Rosemary{1%teaspoon} leaves from stems (2 tsp for 4 servings); finely chop leaves. @Lemon{1} zest and quarter. Cut @Broccoli Florets{8%ounce} into 1-inch pieces, if necessary; toss on a second baking sheet with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on middle rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== Chicken ==

While broccoli roasts, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} and set aside to rest.

== Balsamic Fig Pan Sauce ==

To same pan over medium heat, add shallot, chopped rosemary, and a drizzle of olive oil. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon} and @Fig Jam{2%tablespoon}. Simmer until syrupy, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup} (⅓ cup for 4 servings). Cook until thick and glossy, ~{2-3%minutes}. 

> TIP: Add a splash of water if sauce is too thick.

Turn off heat; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4). Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Once broccoli is done, remove from oven and toss with lemon zest.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise. Divide chicken, potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Drizzle chicken with sauce. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.